TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Finding Certain Weakly-Efficient Vertices in Multiple Objective Linear Fractional Programming
AU  - Benson, Harold P.
Y1  - 1985/02/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.31.2.240
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.31.2.240
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 240
EP  - 248
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Recently Kornbluth and Steuer have developed a simplex-based algorithm for finding all weakly-efficient vertices of an augmented feasible region of a multiple objective linear fractional programming problem. As part of this algorithm, they presented a method for detecting certain weakly-efficient vertices called break points. In this note we show that the procedure used by Kornbluth and Steuer in this method for computing the numbers needed to find these break points may sometimes fail. We also propose a fail-safe method for computing these numbers and give some computational results with this method.
AB  - Recently Kornbluth and Steuer have developed a simplex-based algorithm for finding all weakly-efficient vertices of an augmented feasible region of a multiple objective linear fractional programming problem. As part of this algorithm, they presented a method for detecting certain weakly-efficient vertices called break points. In this note we show that the procedure used by Kornbluth and Steuer in this method for computing the numbers needed to find these break points may sometimes fail. We also propose a fail-safe method for computing these numbers and give some computational results with this method.
